<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="2361" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="11.[138,243,691,715]" box="[138,243,691,715]" pageId="11" pageNumber="2361">
<emphasis box="[138,243,691,715]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="2361">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[138,1185,739,893]" pageId="11" pageNumber="2361">
<emphasis box="[138,217,739,763]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="2361">Adults.</emphasis>
All dorsal setae, except for 
<emphasis box="[563,587,740,763]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="2361">υe</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[653,679,739,763]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="2361">sci</emphasis>
, are lanceolate with finely serrated edges. Setae 
<emphasis box="[208,234,772,796]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="2361">sci</emphasis>
are long and slightly serrate, and although not mentioned in the description, setae 
<emphasis box="[138,162,805,828]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="2361">υe</emphasis>
may also be serrate, but are as slender as 
<emphasis box="[661,687,804,828]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="2361">sci</emphasis>
. Rest of features as for genus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[138,1185,739,893]" pageId="11" pageNumber="2361">
This species was found on 
<taxonomicName box="[514,580,837,861]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rutaceae" genus="Citrus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="11" pageNumber="2361" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[514,580,837,861]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="2361">Citrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. at Hectorspruit (Mpumalanga) and Bindura (
<collectingCountry box="[146,278,869,893]" name="Zimbabwe" pageId="11" pageNumber="2361">Zimbabwe</collectingCountry>
).
</paragraph>
